The container of the liquid nitrogen target was
made of a mylar sheet of 5 mm in thickness, and
its size was 30 mm in radius and 57 mm in length.

formula was applied to yields per equivalent
Systematic errors were amounted to be about

Deuterons produced from the target container were
corrected for using the empty target run.
of deuterons from nitrogen have been measured at
laboratory angles of 43 and 50 degree, and for
maximum energies of the bremsstrahlung photon beam
of 725, 775, and 825 MeV. The double differential
cross sections of deuterons emitted from nitrogen
were obtained for photon energies of 750 and 800 MeV
and for laboratory angles of 43 and 50 degree.
The photon energy was determined by the photon
subtraction method. Results were examined by a
pi-0 photoproduction process off a quasi-deuteron
in nitrogen (gamma+d -> pi-0+d) and by a two-step
process. The two-step process means the following:
first, a nucleon is produced by a photo-pion
production process from a quasi-free nucleon in
the nitrogen nucleus (gamma + "N" -> pi + N); second,
the nucleon produced at the first step picks up
another nucleon in the nucleus and then a deuteron
